le?language=EN>Peoni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 7:48:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Gear?</span><hr size=1> Unless you can twink, you will find it very difficult to afford items that will allow you both a high wisdom score and resists.<br><br>The most important resist is MR, i'd suggest you get whatever MR pieces you can obtain and then add wisdom items to your other locations.<br><br>Peoni<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/8/01 5:26:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Gear?</span><hr size=1> Most of my equip has high amounts of wisdom for particular slots .. ie epic, 10 wis hat, 15 wis range (etc). This leaves you with alot of slots to play with to use for ac/hp/resists. If your trying to balance it (and if you can afford it) do the same. It's do-able .. i started with 90 wis base and still have 210 wis + 120 in all resists now through putting high wis stuff in certain slots <p>Maani<br>58 Preserver<br><a href="http://www.che.nildram.co.uk" style="text-decoration=none">Guild Innit</a><br><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoyoteblack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteblack</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/25/01 12:50:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Gear?</span><hr size=1> Thank guys/Gals for the info!! you to Trueleaf . <p>" No matter how subtle the wizard, a knife between the shoulder blades will seriously cramp his style"  -- Vlad Taltos</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthyroidz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thyroidz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 8:26:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Gear?</span><hr size=1> Im only a lv24 Druid. Just starting to Pk and *cough* get Pked... and with my Wis gear... Im relizing i gotta balance it a lil less wis for ac/mr. (tallon zek btw) I got about, 5k with almost half my gear already. could anyone make a list of good items for my druid? (and maybe even a full list, thx) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uspyder001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spyder001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/30/02 4:28:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Gear?</span><hr size=1> You will want wis gear, magic resist is just about as important as wis gear, so balance these two.  Next is poison resist gear in my opinion, because it doesnt take much poison resist to start totally resisting any player poison spells for some reason.  Then fire, cold, disease.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthyroidz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thyroidz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/30/02 7:09:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Gear?</span><hr size=1> whats the Best search engine for druid items? everlore? eqdruids items?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showPrevMessage?topicID=28.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showNextMessage?topicID=28.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.emailToFriend?topicID=28.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.threadControl?topicID=28.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=28.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http: